<HEADLINE>
FT  01 SEP 94 / Observer: Vasco da gaffa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Premier Li may be forgiven for thinking that the local press has it in for
him. In the Portuguese colony of <LOCATION>Macao</LOCATION>, hacks have just landed an
uncomfortable exclusive, c/o the office of General <PERSON>Vasco Rocha Vieira</PERSON>, the
governor.
His officials have compiled a profile of Li, describing him as arrogant and
incompetent. Of course, it was intended for the general only. But you can't
keep a grubby hack down.
Very poor show, not least because the general is now on an eight-day
official trip to <LOCATION>China</LOCATION>, where today he will meet Li. Even more poor show,
<LOCATION>Macao</LOCATION> - a Portuguese colony since <DATE>1557</DATE> - is due to revert to Chinese rule in
<DATE>1999</DATE>.
Still, five years should be enough for the general to find himself another
job.
</TEXT>
