<LEADPARA>  When the people running San Jose's City Lights Theater Company put on a
fund-raising show last night for their new theater at 529 S. Second St., they
reached, naturally, for the city lights. Their show -- a Robin Hood theme done
over a roast pig dinner -- happened after our deadline. But we managed to get
a sneak preview from the cast. Queen Elinore was played by former Supervisor
Susanne Wilson, who was required to give a toast about making babies. The
nasty Prince John was played by San Jose Rep founder and World Festival
promoter Jim Reber. In a stroke of inspired casting, the sheriff of Nottingham
was played by San Jose Auditor Jerry Silva. Maid Marion was played by
Stephanie Schiro, who described herself jestingly as the "bimbo of Sherwood
Forest." And the rest of the cast included Mercury News City Editor Charlie
McCollum, Metro publisher David Cohen, Sunnyvale Councilman Larry Stone,
Downtown Directory publisher David Katz and our own Leigh Weimers, who played
the earl of Nottinghamshire, a nobleman known for having perfected the art of
torture.  </LEADPARA>
