FT  17 DEC 92 / Portugal lifts capital controls
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LISBON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The <ORGANIZATION>Bank of Portugal</ORGANIZATION> yesterday announced it was immediately lifting
restrictions on capital movements, two weeks ahead of schedule, AP reports
from <LOCATION>Lisbon</LOCATION>.
The lifting of controls allows foreigners to operate in <LOCATION>Portugal</LOCATION>'s
short-term money market and enables domestic banks to lend escudos to
non-residents, said <PERSON>Mr Vasco Pereira</PERSON>, director of the central bank's foreign
department.
